1299 games version is only work for this board

This boards use A13 SOC from Allwinner

256MB DDR, support 15khz CRT monitors and 800x600 VGA display

2600 games version is only work for this board

This boards use H3 SOC from Allwinner

256MB DDR, support 15khz CRT monitors and 1280x720 VGA/HDMI display
fqas.title: Which board is working

fqas.text:
Note: this method only used for 2600 version, and because the encrypt mechanism of my supplier, the TF card can not swap, or the board will not boot, so please try to back up all data in your TF card before you editing of your TF card.

There are 2 partitions in the TF card, the 1st is of FAT format , the 2nd is of EXT3 format;

The 1st partition stores some boot files and configuration files

The 2st partition stores a Linux root file system, programs and games, some programs may has been encrypted by my supplier.

Actually , the program supports 4 languages:

         cn -- Simple Chinese

         en -- English

         tw -- Traditional Chinese

         ko -- Korean

And it supports 2 resolutions:

          1280x720 -- for HDMI/VGA

          384x224 -- for 15kHz CRT monitors

          So , there are 4 gamelists, for English, only consider files

                  '/opt/UIs/en/1280x720/gamelist.json' for 720P

                  '/opt/UIs/en/384x224/gamelist.json' for CGA

Main frontend is file '/opt/bin/sdlfe', it loads file '/opt/bin/gamelib.json' for loading info of rom

gamelist.json fromat:

     this json file is a list of all games

     every games has 2 fields:

         rom -- fronted use this field as key to find more info in '/opt/bin/gamelib.json'

         wname -- a list of unicode of game display name

             NOTE: all available characters is in /opt/UIs/en/1280x720/config/images/name_select_fonts.png and /opt/UIs/en/1280x720/config/images/name_unselect_fonts.png, if you use unavailable characters, frontend will crash.

gamelib.json fromat:

     this json file is a map of all roms

     key is rom

     every rom has the following fields:

         "emu" : emu app no

         "engine" : emu director

             if 'emu' equals 5 and 'engine' equals "2222", frontend will call /opt/2222/bins/app6 for this rom

             if 'engine' equals "1300-mame", frontend will call /opt/1300/bins/app6 for this rom

                 app1 -- FBA

                 app2 -- FBA

                 app3 -- FBA

                 app4 -- FBA

                 app5 -- FBA

                 app6 -- MAME

                 app7 -- FBA

                 app8 -- PS1

                 app9 -- SFC

         "gameitem" : the game parameters, it actually is a byte array, and it is of BASE64 format, MAME, PS1, SFC games may need not this field

         "lev" : boolean typed, determine whether this game have difficult level

         "life" : boolean typed, determine whether this game have life

             all game option game is in /opt/nvram

             all game ROMs is in /opt/roms

             all PS1 game ROMs is in /opt/romsp

         "type" : string typed, determine game's type , determine which icon will display before gamename

fqas.text: Modify file '/usr/myinit' of the second partition, try to comment the commands for play boot video and logo video.

fqas.text:
The J36 on the A13 PCB is the pins for debug serial port.

  • pin1 -- Rxd
  • pin2 -- Txd
  • pin3 -- 3.3V (Not connect)
  • pin4 -- Gnd

Debug Serial port configuration : 115200 8N1

Users can connect serial port to check debug information, and login in Linux system to run commands.

The 3pin above the TF cards solt of the H3 PCB is the debug serial port
